Review: All acceptance criteria met. Fixed critical upsertSubscription bug where missing user_id would cause NOT NULL violations on webhook processing.
- [critical] upsertSubscription() did not include user_id in the upsert payload and used stripe_subscription_id as conflict key. Since getOrCreateCustomer creates the initial row without stripe_subscription_id, webhook-driven upserts would attempt an INSERT without user_id, violating the NOT NULL constraint. Fixed by looking up user_id from existing row by stripe_customer_id and using user_id as conflict key. (fixed)
- [info] customers.ts getOrCreateCustomer does not check the error result from the DB upsert call. In production, a failed upsert would silently return the Stripe customer ID even if the DB row wasn't created. Low risk since the upsert uses onConflict and the schema is simple. (unfixed)
- [info] Subscription type is duplicated between packages/billing/src/types.ts and packages/db/src/types.ts (SubscriptionRow). Consider having billing re-export from @repo/db/types to avoid drift. (unfixed)